headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum knew he was sitting on 48 points entering the final minute of the Boston Celtics' Martin Luther King Jr. Day matinee against the Charlotte Hornets on Monday and briefly thought about backing the ball out and letting the clock run down...
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 51, Celtics beat Hornets for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday and the Milwaukee Bucks responded to the Indiana Pacers' fast start by delivering a dominant performance down the stretch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday sparks late rally as Bucks beat Pacers 132-119

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland has developed a knack for when it's time for him to take over a game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 30 to push Cavaliers past Pelicans 113-103

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett's end-to-end driving dunk with 0.6 seconds left in regulation had the basket shaking.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors recover after Barrett tying slam, edge Knicks in OT

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 41 points and Jordan Poole added 32 points to help the wobbling Golden State Warriors to a 127-118 win over the Washington Wizards on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Poole lead Warriors to 127-118 win against Wizards

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 12 of his 28 points in the final period as the Atlanta Hawks held off Miami's comeback attempt and beat the Heat 121-113 on Monday for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's 28 help hot-shooting Hawks hold off Heat, 121-113

headlines.description: — Walker Kessler had career-highs of 20 points and 21 rebounds, Jordan Clarkson added 21 points and the Utah Jazz rallied from a 10-point deficit in the fourth quarter to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 126-125 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kessler's 20 points, 21 rebounds help Jazz beat T-Wolves

headlines.description: — The Memphis Grizzlies are making lengthy winning streaks an annual occurrence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies beat Suns 136-106, extend winning streak to 10

events.name: Houston Rockets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had a season-high 48 points, nine assists and eight rebounds in his third 40-point performance since turning 38 less than three weeks ago, and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped a three-game skid with a 140-132 victory over the Houston...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron drops 48, Lakers beat Rockets 140-132 to snap skid
